The paper deals with the problem of rendezvous in trees, which involves mobile agents moving in a graph. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the study of memory requirements for solving the problem, which is related to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of synchronous rounds and the exploration problem with compact automata suggests a connection to Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the use of identical agents and deterministic solutions, which are related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
